OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1775981091
OL,3,CFurther motorway closures due to
OL,4,Cprotests as fuel stations run dry
OL,6,FThe protests have caused disruption to
OL,7,Fsome bus routes across Ireland and
OL,8,Fwithin the capital, where Luas Green
OL,9,FLine tram services are also affected.
OL,11,FParticipants say the Government needs
OL,12,Fto take urgent action on fuel prices
OL,13,For they will go out of business.
OL,15,FProtesters have blockaded the
OL,16,Fcountry's only oil refinery, in
OL,17,FWhitegate, Co Cork, as well as key
OL,18,Fdepots in Galway and Foynes, Co
OL,19,FLimerick.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1775981091
OL,3,CFurther motorway closures due to
OL,4,Cprotests as fuel stations run dry
OL,6,FThere have also been concerns about
OL,7,Ffuel shortages leading to curtailments
OL,8,Fon the provision of emergency services
OL,9,Fand the delivery of vital goods, while
OL,10,Fthe National Emergency Coordination
OL,11,FGroup urged the public to only buy the
OL,12,Ffuel they need.
OL,14,FTaoiseach Micheal Martin warned that
OL,15,FIreland is on the "precipice of
OL,16,Fturning oil away from the country",
OL,17,Fdescribing the situation as
OL,18,F"unconscionable", "illogical", and
OL,19,F"difficult to comprehend".
OL,26,@wD@SOUxD@bO]zD@AOUzD@PO]zD@SOUzD@]O]{D@
OL,26,AAOU{D@YO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/12
